description = Retrieve, capture, or refresh distilled prompt-engineering knowledge — composing the instruction itself: clarity and structure, few-shot exemplars, reasoning elicitation (chain-of-thought), output-format wording, and prompt-level task decomposition. Use when wording or structuring a prompt to steer model behavior, choosing exemplars, or looking up or saving a prompt-engineering technique — not when managing what fills the context window (that is context-engineering), nor when designing a tool's description, schema, or enforced structured output (that is tool-design).
